President Barack Obama has proclaimed May as National Physical Fitness and Sports Month. He emphasizes the importance of leading an active and healthy lifestyle for the well-being of citizens. Regular physical activity and nutritious meals can help prevent chronic diseases such as cancer, heart disease, and stroke. The Obama administration is committed to promoting a healthy lifestyle through initiatives like Let's Move! and the President's Council on Fitness, Sports, and Nutrition. They are working to provide Americans with the tools and information they need to maintain a healthy lifestyle. The proclamation encourages individuals, families, schools, and communities to prioritize physical activity, sports participation, and good nutrition.